results.name: Number of complete strict planar branching factorizations of n.
comment: A strict planar branching factorization of n is either the number n itself or a sequence of at least two strict planar branching factorizations, one of each factor in a strict ordered factorization of n. A strict planar branching factorization is complete if the leaves are all prime numbers.
formula: a(product of n distinct primes) = A032037(n).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 11 2018
